# initiallyInactive

**Type Property**

The newly created queue is inactive.

## Declaration

```swift
static let initiallyInactive: DispatchQueue.Attributes
```

## Discussion

Normally, a newly created queue schedules submitted blocks for execution immediately. Use this attribute to prevent the queue from scheduling blocks until you call its [doc://com.apple.dispatch/documentation/Dispatch/DispatchObject/activate()] method.

## Attributes

- **concurrent**: The queue schedules tasks concurrently.
